  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Living Wage Research</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project will undertake a data analysis to understand the number of jobs in Wales paying the Living Wage and use a desktop study to analyse the impact on the economy, poverty and inequality if all jobs in Wales were paid the Living Wage, and the difference between that and jobs paying the National Living Wage.    It will look at three areas: Wales as a whole, the Cardiff Capital Region and Merthyr Tydfil.  The former areas will see a data analysis and case studies, followed by a &quot;Living Wage Summit&quot; to disseminate the information.  The latter will also include engagement with businesses who do and don&apos;t pay the Living Wage, with a practical attempt to increase the number of businesses paying the Living Wage.</narrative>
  </description>
